title: Missing Hull teenagers 'believed to be in West Yorkshire'
text:
Police in Hull say two teenage girls who were reported missing last Friday are believed to be in West Yorkshire.
Samantha Davies (L) and Lauren Johnson have been missing since Friday. Credit: Humberside Police Samantha Davies, 16, and Lauren Johnson, 17, reportedly travelled together by taxi to the Huddersfield area.
Police say they are still in the Huddersfield, Featherstone or Wakefield area.
There are concerns for the girls' safety and they are being urged to get in touch.
Samantha is described as white, 5ft 6ins tall with a slim build and she has very long straight ginger hair. Lauren is described as white, 5ft 4ins tall with a slim build and she has very long dark brown hair. Hull East Yorkshire
